/// @name Spacing(owl)
/// @author Tyler Benton
/// @page objects/spacing
/// @decsription
/// This is a helper mixin for using the [lobotomized owl selector](http://alistapart.com/article/axiomatic-css-and-lobotomized-owls).
///
/// @state .o-spacing--off - Resets the margin-top to what it was originally, without the Lobotomized Owl selector
/// @state .o-spacing--compact - Used to make sections compact when needed. Only targets direct descendants.
/// @state .o-spacing--sm - Is similar to `.o-spacing--compact` but it will apply to all children elements
/// @state .o-spacing--md - The default size for the spacing selector
/// @state .o-spacing--lg - Adds a larger space between elements(Affects all children)
/// @state .o-spacing--expanded - Adds more spacing between sections. Only targets direct descendants.
///
/// @markup
/// <div class=${@state}>
